      <hedline>
        <hl1>Life Under the Billboard Blanket</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Joyce Fuller letter disputes David W Dunlap's April 16 article on NYC's massive billboards (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Why shouldn't individual citizens of the city be paid for the encroachment of advertising on their time, their thoughts, their spirits?</p>
        <p>I would also like to be compensated for the time I spend disposing of mail and telephone solicitations.</p>
        <p>JOYCE FULLER  Chelsea</p>
      </block>
